==================================================\
JOIN ID NORMALIZATION\
==================================================\
\
Create a single standardized JOIN_ID across all files.\
\
Rules:\
- strip whitespace\
- if value looks like Excel float: 12345.0 -> 12345\
- handle scientific notation safely if possible\
- extract digits only\
- zero-pad to 10 digits\
- preserve original raw ID columns too\
\
Implement a reusable function like:\
\
def normalize_join_id(x):\
    if missing -> return pd.NA\
    s = str(x).strip()\
    if regex fullmatch r'\\d+\\.0+' -> remove trailing .0\
    else try float conversion only if obviously numeric-like\
    digits = re.sub(r'\\D', '', s)\
    if digits == '' -> pd.NA\
    return digits.zfill(10)\
\
Report:\
- percent missing JOIN_ID by dataset\
- raw ID length distribution\
- normalized ID length distribution\
- top issue types\
\
